column6: Rebecca Wright is the Director of DIMACS, an institute of Discrete Mathematics and Computer Science Research at Rutgers University. This institution runs a special focus on cybersecurity, and REU program for undergraduate students, as well as numerous outreach programs for middle schoolers and young women interested in computing. Additionally, Dr. Wright is on the board of CRA-W, is a professor in the Department of Computer Science at Rutgers University focusing on topics in privacy, cryptographic protocols, and fault-tolerant distributed computing.
